HEADWORD: Curarine
<hw>Cu"ra*rine</hw> <pr>(k?"r?-r?n ⟦or⟧ k?-r?"r?n; 104)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A deadly alkaloid extracted from
the curare poison and from the <spn>Strychnos toxifera</spn>. It is
obtained in crystalline colorless salts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

